Program: Outlook
Title: Life After Hurricane Katrina in New Orleans
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbs2m
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Singer Charmaine Neville on rebuilding her house after Hurricane Katrina in the US, and a look at why so few people have been able to return home. Also, Mechai Viravaidya and how his family planning promotion has saved 7 million lives in Thailand. Repatriation of 300,000 returning refugees in Liberia after 14 years of civil war. Finally, why 3 men want to run 3000k across the Sahara Desert in 75 days. Show less